  "text": "Finally, Twitter is used by about 10% of the US population (Pew Research Center, 2013) which is certainly far, far from a representative sample. While Facebook has a wider diffusion rate, its rates of use are structured by race, gender, class and other factors and are also not representative [CITATION_1] (Allison, 2001; Dunning and Freeman, 2007) .",
